goals.question: What is the distribution of vowel count in the state capitals?

goals.question: What is the relationship between longitude and vowel count?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], c=data['vowel_count'], cmap='viridis', label='State Capitals')
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_capitals_count = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_capitals_count.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6))
    plt.title('Which state has the most state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Count of State Capitals')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['State Capitals Count'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    first_letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts()
    first_letter_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', edgecolor='k')
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of first letters of the state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('First Letter')
    plt.ylabel('Count of State Capitals')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['vowel_count'], bins=range(2, 8), color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Vowel Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of vowel count in the state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Vowel Count'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['vowel_count'], c=data['vowel_count'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Vowel Count')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between longitude and vowel count?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Vowel Count")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
